Australia's **Stage 3 income tax cuts** took effect on 1 July 2024, reducing the rate on incomes between $18,201 and $45,000 from 19% to 16%, and the rate on incomes from $45,001 to $135,000 from 32.5% to 30%. The top rate of 45% still applies above $190,000.

This calculator uses the **ATO's FY2025–26 tax brackets** — the same rates that apply for the year ending 30 June 2026. Enter your taxable income to see income tax payable, 2% Medicare levy, LITO offset applied, effective tax rate, and estimated annual take-home pay.
